In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims July 15 through July 21, 2012, as Captive Nations Week. He emphasizes the enduring bonds between the United States and those who strive for freedom and justice around the world. He acknowledges the courage of individuals who protest for reform and defy censorship. The Obama Administration condemns tyranny and supports emerging democracies, working with international partners to advance human rights and prosperity. The proclamation also mentions that the Congress authorized and requested the President to designate the third week of July each year as Captive Nations Week. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to reaffirm their commitment to freedom, dignity, and opportunity for all.